(27 Oct 1997) T/I:   11:12:45    GS 10:27:14
Some 2,000 members of the Church of Scientology demonstrated Monday (27/10) in Berlin for religious freedom on the eve of a court ruling on whether the group was a religion or a business. Scientologists worldwide, especially in the United States, have said German measures against the group are undemocratic and smack of Nazi-style suppression.
SHOWS:
BERLIN, GERMANY, 26/10
00.00 Pan down buildings to crowd in square;
00.09 CU poster: "End Government discrimination";
00.12 WS crowd waving flags and cheering;
00.18 MS preacher addressing crowd from stage;
00.22 SOT Isaac Hayes, US actor and singer: "In this day and age - in this time in the world, this kind of action cannot be tolerated and we will keep coming back and keep demonstrating, to let the world know it is wrong."
00.37 Woman dressed as Statue of Liberty, as crowd sings: "Break down the wall of intolerance....break down the wall of intolerance and set your people free."
00.45 Front of march to Brandenburg gate, chanting "Religious freedom now;
00.51 Side shot march;
00.57 Night shot stage with band playing "Freedom";
01.04 Pan crowd;
01.08 WS stage in front of Brandenburg Gate;
01.14 VISION ENDS

