(1 Apr 1997) T/I 10:17:07


The bodies of 39 people who died in the Heaven's Gate cult mass
suicide in southern California were released on Monday (31/03)by
authorities in southern California.
San Diego County medical examiner Dr. Brian Blackbourne told
reporters that autopsies had been completed and that the bodies
were being transported to mortuaries around the country.


SHOWS: 

